00:09:24.831 --> 00:09:28.368 align:middle line:84%
OK. So you ended up-- you
were-- when you were young,

00:09:28.368 --> 00:09:31.038 align:middle line:84%
you were still new in
your career and you ended

00:09:31.038 --> 00:09:33.473 align:middle line:84%
up as an attorney
with the World Bank.

00:09:33.473 --> 00:09:34.841 align:middle line:90%
Is that correct?

00:09:34.841 --> 00:09:37.744 align:middle line:84%
And it's kind of an interesting
story but how you got there,

00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.646 align:middle line:84%
who brought you in,
and who you've been

00:09:39.646 --> 00:09:41.481 align:middle line:84%
in alignment with
this whole time.

00:09:41.481 --> 00:09:43.383 align:middle line:84%
Give us a little bit of
the back story there.

00:09:43.383 --> 00:09:44.651 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: OK.

00:09:44.651 --> 00:09:47.487 align:middle line:84%
Well, first of all, as I
told you all, I'm persistent.

00:09:47.487 --> 00:09:50.957 align:middle line:84%
So I got hired on
my fifth interview.

00:09:50.957 --> 00:09:53.927 align:middle line:84%
My first interview was
right out of law school

00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:56.396 align:middle line:84%
because I studied
development economics.

00:09:56.396 --> 00:10:00.867 align:middle line:84%
And if you're a lawyer and
you want to fight poverty,

00:10:00.867 --> 00:10:02.169 align:middle line:84%
the World Bank is
the place to go.

00:10:02.169 --> 00:10:06.106 align:middle line:84%
That's where you can be both
a lawyer and an economist.

00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:11.144 align:middle line:84%
So, they said, "Well, Karen,
you may know a little bit,

00:10:11.144 --> 00:10:13.613 align:middle line:84%
but you've never really
worked as a professional.

00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:17.117 align:middle line:84%
Go get your-- go learn
how to be a lawyer."

00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:20.821 align:middle line:84%
So I went to a big law
firm, Wall Street law firm,

00:10:20.821 --> 00:10:22.789 align:middle line:90%
and I learned securities law.

00:10:22.789 --> 00:10:24.725 align:middle line:84%
And then I went back
and they said, "Well,

00:10:24.725 --> 00:10:28.095 align:middle line:84%
you may know securities
law but you never worked

00:10:28.095 --> 00:10:29.529 align:middle line:90%
for a financial institution."

00:10:29.529 --> 00:10:32.065 align:middle line:84%
So I went to US Export-Import
Bank

00:10:32.065 --> 00:10:36.169 align:middle line:84%
which finances one-third
the amount of the World Bank

00:10:36.169 --> 00:10:39.172 align:middle line:84%
but what it is is it's
financing exports.

00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:40.507 align:middle line:90%
They called it Boeing's Bank.

00:10:40.507 --> 00:10:43.643 align:middle line:84%
We were financing
the sale of aircraft.

00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:44.845 align:middle line:90%
And so I did that.

00:10:44.845 --> 00:10:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And then I went back and,
you know, you don't need

00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:49.049 align:middle line:84%
to make a whole long
story short.

00:10:49.049 --> 00:10:52.319 align:middle line:84%
One time, one of the people
in the interview found

00:10:52.319 --> 00:10:55.822 align:middle line:84%
out that my mother who was an
elementary school principal had

00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:59.860 align:middle line:84%
lectured this man because his
daughter was getting frightened

00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:01.294 align:middle line:90%
of math.

00:11:01.294 --> 00:11:04.264 align:middle line:84%
And so, when he said, "Is your
mother Sylvia Hudes [assumed

00:11:04.264 --> 00:11:06.433 align:middle line:84%
spelling]" I said, "Yes",
and I could see by his face

00:11:06.433 --> 00:11:07.934 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't I get
the job that time.

00:11:07.934 --> 00:11:10.670 align:middle line:84%
But, anyway, so I went
back another time.

00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:12.005 align:middle line:90%
And that time was good.

00:11:12.005 --> 00:11:15.242 align:middle line:84%
And the person who brought
me in was Ibrahim Shihata

00:11:15.242 --> 00:11:18.645 align:middle line:84%
who was an Egyptian
who had worked at OPEC

00:11:18.645 --> 00:11:21.782 align:middle line:84%
and became the World
Bank General Counsel.

00:11:21.782 --> 00:11:24.184 align:middle line:90%
And so he hired me.

00:11:24.184 --> 00:11:26.620 align:middle line:84%
And the very first thing
he did was he put me

00:11:26.620 --> 00:11:29.289 align:middle line:84%
on the Jordan desk
and the Yemen desk.

00:11:29.289 --> 00:11:32.859 align:middle line:84%
And I worked very happily in
the Middle East for 10 years.

00:11:32.859 --> 00:11:34.461 align:middle line:90%
And then he reassigned me

00:11:34.461 --> 00:11:38.064 align:middle line:84%
because I started reporting
corruption in Yemen.

00:11:38.064 --> 00:11:39.065 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:11:39.065 --> 00:11:40.801 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So you started
at what year?

00:11:40.801 --> 00:11:42.369 align:middle line:90%
When you started reporting the--

00:11:42.369 --> 00:11:45.038 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: I went to the
Word Bank in 1986.

00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:45.872 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:11:45.872 --> 00:11:49.876 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: And it was in 95 that--

00:11:49.876 --> 00:11:51.044 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:53.380 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: I started reporting
corruption in Yemen.

00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:55.382 align:middle line:84%
And so I was moved
to the Philippines.

00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:58.218 align:middle line:84%
And then I started reporting
corruption in the Philippines.

00:11:58.218 --> 00:12:00.187 align:middle line:90%
I have a sixth sense for--

00:12:00.187 --> 00:12:01.121 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:12:01.121 --> 00:12:01.655 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: -- corruption.

00:12:01.655 --> 00:12:02.756 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:12:02.756 --> 00:12:04.491 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm sure they're
saying, "Oh, my God,

00:12:04.491 --> 00:12:06.927 align:middle line:84%
who was responsible
for bringing her in?"

00:12:06.927 --> 00:12:09.696 align:middle line:84%
OK. Now, what we're going
to do is take a look

00:12:09.696 --> 00:12:11.998 align:middle line:84%
at the institution
itself because, again,

00:12:11.998 --> 00:12:13.934 align:middle line:84%
most people are really
not very clear

00:12:13.934 --> 00:12:17.304 align:middle line:84%
on what the World Bank
is, what the IMF is.

00:12:17.304 --> 00:12:22.409 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to show a short
historical film that talks

00:12:22.409 --> 00:12:26.413 align:middle line:84%
about the origination
of the World Bank,

00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:28.582 align:middle line:90%
and this was in 1944, OK?

00:12:28.582 --> 00:12:30.483 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:12:30.483 --> 00:12:34.020 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

