00:14:03.977 --> 00:14:06.546 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Well, it's a lovely
public relation piece

00:14:06.546 --> 00:14:08.114 align:middle line:90%
from the very beginning.

00:14:08.114 --> 00:14:14.721 align:middle line:84%
And how far has the
agenda actually dropped off

00:14:14.721 --> 00:14:17.624 align:middle line:84%
from what we just saw there
are stayed true to what we--

00:14:17.624 --> 00:14:20.026 align:middle line:84%
it could mean we'd looked
the world at large and say,

00:14:20.026 --> 00:14:21.361 align:middle line:90%
"Well, that didn't happen."

00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.129 align:middle line:84%
But you say, "Yeah,
actually some

00:14:23.129 --> 00:14:24.364 align:middle line:90%
of this has been accomplished."

00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:25.699 align:middle line:90%
Let's to talk about that.

00:14:25.699 --> 00:14:29.302 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Well, there were 44
countries in that conference.

00:14:29.302 --> 00:14:32.606 align:middle line:84%
There are now 188
countries that are members

00:14:32.606 --> 00:14:34.574 align:middle line:90%
of the World Bank and IMF.

00:14:34.574 --> 00:14:38.611 align:middle line:84%
They're talking about trying
to prevent a world war

00:14:38.611 --> 00:14:43.183 align:middle line:84%
because of currencies
being out of control.

00:14:43.183 --> 00:14:45.952 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
we are right now.

00:14:45.952 --> 00:14:50.623 align:middle line:84%
We're preventing World War
III because, for example,

00:14:50.623 --> 00:14:53.660 align:middle line:84%
the Federal Reserve
Board has refused

00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:55.729 align:middle line:90%
to give Germany back its gold.

00:14:55.729 --> 00:14:56.663 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:14:56.663 --> 00:14:58.131 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: That's an act of war.

00:14:58.131 --> 00:14:59.265 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:14:59.265 --> 00:15:00.266 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how they've
gotten away with that.

00:15:00.266 --> 00:15:01.601 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: We are--

00:15:01.601 --> 00:15:02.769 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Seven years they said
before they're going to be--

00:15:02.769 --> 00:15:03.470 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Yes.

00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:04.537 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: -- taken care of.

00:15:04.537 --> 00:15:05.939 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: We are on the
very edge of a war.

00:15:05.939 --> 00:15:09.309 align:middle line:84%
And I'm happy to tell you that
we're not going to have a war

00:15:09.309 --> 00:15:13.146 align:middle line:84%
because of the Bretton Woods
Institutions, because all,

00:15:13.146 --> 00:15:18.651 align:middle line:84%
188 ministers have
reinstated me as the lawyer

00:15:18.651 --> 00:15:22.288 align:middle line:90%
who understands what's going on.

00:15:22.288 --> 00:15:26.092 align:middle line:84%
When you have 188
countries in an organization,

00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:28.161 align:middle line:84%
you have to pay attention
to them.

00:15:28.161 --> 00:15:30.997 align:middle line:84%
And what's happened
is there was a rule,

00:15:30.997 --> 00:15:32.665 align:middle line:84%
called the Gentlemen's
Agreement.

00:15:32.665 --> 00:15:35.001 align:middle line:84%
That the United States
could appoint the president

00:15:35.001 --> 00:15:38.271 align:middle line:84%
of the World Bank and the
Europeans could appoint the

00:15:38.271 --> 00:15:40.073 align:middle line:90%
managing director of the IMF.

00:15:40.073 --> 00:15:42.442 align:middle line:90%
This lasted for 66 years.

00:15:42.442 --> 00:15:49.749 align:middle line:84%
And in 2004, I learned that if
the United States didn't stop

00:15:49.749 --> 00:15:52.585 align:middle line:84%
all of this corruption,
that we were going

00:15:52.585 --> 00:15:53.920 align:middle line:84%
to lose the Gentlemen's
Agreement.

00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:57.057 align:middle line:84%
That was a very accurate
stakeholder analysis

00:15:57.057 --> 00:15:59.426 align:middle line:84%
that I saw this was
going to happen.

00:15:59.426 --> 00:16:02.529 align:middle line:84%
And I started trying to
get the problem solved.

00:16:02.529 --> 00:16:03.930 align:middle line:84%
I did what a lawyer
is supposed to do.

00:16:03.930 --> 00:16:05.398 align:middle line:90%
I went to the audit committee.

00:16:05.398 --> 00:16:08.435 align:middle line:84%
I stayed internally
inside the World Bank.

00:16:08.435 --> 00:16:13.073 align:middle line:84%
And finally in 2007, I went
to the Treasury Department.

00:16:13.073 --> 00:16:14.808 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Treasury
Department

00:16:14.808 --> 00:16:17.644 align:middle line:84%
through Larry Summers,
whose child was

00:16:17.644 --> 00:16:20.647 align:middle line:84%
in the same elementary
school class as mine.

00:16:20.647 --> 00:16:25.485 align:middle line:84%
I would see him at a PTA meeting
and I would start harassing him

00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:26.953 align:middle line:84%
because I knew that
we were going

00:16:26.953 --> 00:16:28.755 align:middle line:84%
to lose the Gentlemen's
Agreement.

00:16:28.755 --> 00:16:33.293 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough, in 2010,
that's exactly what happened.

00:16:33.293 --> 00:16:35.528 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So if we back up for
a moment, you were trying

00:16:35.528 --> 00:16:36.896 align:middle line:90%
to warn them about this.

00:16:36.896 --> 00:16:39.432 align:middle line:84%
Now, in one level, you know,
listening to it, I'd say, "Well,

00:16:39.432 --> 00:16:42.435 align:middle line:84%
the United States deserves
to lose that position

00:16:42.435 --> 00:16:45.405 align:middle line:84%
if we're operating in-- to
that degree of corruption."

00:16:45.405 --> 00:16:49.442 align:middle line:84%
On another level, you're saying,
"Let's fix the corruption

00:16:49.442 --> 00:16:53.580 align:middle line:84%
so that we can continue to
remain in that position," right?

00:16:53.580 --> 00:16:56.783 align:middle line:84%
I mean, did we deserve to
remain in that position is--

00:16:56.783 --> 00:16:58.585 align:middle line:84%
that's more of an
ethical argument.

00:16:58.585 --> 00:17:01.421 align:middle line:84%
What was your intention
when you first tried

00:17:01.421 --> 00:17:03.223 align:middle line:84%
to bring this to
their attention?

00:17:03.223 --> 00:17:08.794 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Well, in 2006 and 2007,
I was in the US Congress,

00:17:08.794 --> 00:17:10.129 align:middle line:90%
all over the US Congress.

00:17:10.129 --> 00:17:12.365 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Senate
Committee on Foreign Relations,

00:17:12.365 --> 00:17:16.536 align:middle line:84%
that was then shared by Joe
Biden with Hillary Clinton

00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:19.205 align:middle line:84%
and Barack Obama
as junior senators.

00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:23.176 align:middle line:84%
I went to the senate
Committee on Finance.

00:17:23.176 --> 00:17:28.314 align:middle line:84%
And what was very interesting
was Senator Lugar had a series

00:17:28.314 --> 00:17:30.650 align:middle line:90%
of hearings on this corruption.

00:17:30.650 --> 00:17:33.520 align:middle line:84%
And one of the letters that
I wrote to Senator Lugar,

00:17:33.520 --> 00:17:35.221 align:middle line:90%
you can see it on my website,

00:17:35.221 --> 00:17:39.826 align:middle line:84%
was I said the German executive
director on the board said

00:17:39.826 --> 00:17:44.330 align:middle line:84%
that the board is being treated
like mushrooms, kept in the dark

00:17:44.330 --> 00:17:46.833 align:middle line:90%
and fertilizer put on them.

00:17:46.833 --> 00:17:49.435 align:middle line:84%
And that was exactly
what was going

00:17:49.435 --> 00:17:51.037 align:middle line:90%
on with the American public.

00:17:51.037 --> 00:17:54.774 align:middle line:84%
In 2007, I knew that the
public needed to know

00:17:54.774 --> 00:17:57.710 align:middle line:84%
about this corruption to
prevent the United States

00:17:57.710 --> 00:17:59.212 align:middle line:84%
from losing the Gentlemen's
Agreement.

00:17:59.212 --> 00:18:00.747 align:middle line:90%
This is a terrible thing.

00:18:00.747 --> 00:18:04.384 align:middle line:84%
We've lost our moral
leadership in front of all

00:18:04.384 --> 00:18:06.152 align:middle line:90%
of the countries of the world.

00:18:06.152 --> 00:18:07.654 align:middle line:90%
This is a terrible thing.

00:18:07.654 --> 00:18:10.290 align:middle line:84%
And it could have been prevented
and it wasn't presented

00:18:10.290 --> 00:18:12.792 align:middle line:84%
because this super
entity that I was talking

00:18:12.792 --> 00:18:15.562 align:middle line:90%
about owns all of the media.

00:18:15.562 --> 00:18:16.829 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:18:16.829 --> 00:18:18.398 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: And that was why I
couldn't get my story out.

00:18:18.398 --> 00:18:21.868 align:middle line:84%
So the most important thing
that I think your listeners have

00:18:21.868 --> 00:18:26.005 align:middle line:84%
to consider is everything that
I'm telling you all today,

00:18:26.005 --> 00:18:27.974 align:middle line:84%
why didn't you hear
about it earlier?

00:18:27.974 --> 00:18:29.976 align:middle line:84%
You'll see the dates
of the letters.

00:18:29.976 --> 00:18:31.177 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: When people
go to your website--

00:18:31.177 --> 00:18:32.278 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: That's right.

00:18:32.278 --> 00:18:33.413 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- and start
really digging into it.

00:18:33.413 --> 00:18:36.049 align:middle line:84%
You can see-- you have
chronicled everything

00:18:36.049 --> 00:18:38.184 align:middle line:84%
as you said earlier at
the beginning of this.

00:18:38.184 --> 00:18:40.253 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: But also what
happened was,

00:18:40.253 --> 00:18:43.256 align:middle line:84%
it wasn't that the US
Congress was doing nothing.

00:18:43.256 --> 00:18:45.358 align:middle line:90%
The US Congress was asking

00:18:45.358 --> 00:18:49.262 align:middle line:84%
for a government
accountability office inquiry

00:18:49.262 --> 00:18:49.963 align:middle line:90%
into the corruption.

00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:50.797 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:18:50.797 --> 00:18:52.065 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: That happened in 2008.

00:18:52.065 --> 00:18:57.103 align:middle line:84%
And then, in 2010, I went
to Organizing for America.

00:18:57.103 --> 00:19:00.707 align:middle line:84%
That is the group that
is very closely aligned

00:19:00.707 --> 00:19:04.711 align:middle line:84%
with raising funds for the
reelection of Barack Obama.

00:19:04.711 --> 00:19:07.547 align:middle line:84%
And I said, "You will
get bipartisan support

00:19:07.547 --> 00:19:09.382 align:middle line:90%
for fighting this corruption."

00:19:09.382 --> 00:19:13.119 align:middle line:84%
And they went to Senator Lugar
and then they called me back

00:19:13.119 --> 00:19:14.687 align:middle line:90%
and said, "Great, Karen.

00:19:14.687 --> 00:19:16.322 align:middle line:90%
Go to Senator Lugar."

00:19:16.322 --> 00:19:19.259 align:middle line:84%
And Senator Lugar
published a paper

00:19:19.259 --> 00:19:22.161 align:middle line:84%
which said the government
