00:37:49.735 --> 00:37:51.136 align:middle line:90%
in some other regions.

00:37:51.136 --> 00:37:54.706 align:middle line:84%
I mean, was it completely not
foreseen that this would happen

00:37:54.706 --> 00:37:56.541 align:middle line:84%
in Cyprus, Spain,
Italy, et cetera?

00:37:56.541 --> 00:37:59.344 align:middle line:84%
I mean, was this-- this
was a surprise to everyone,

00:37:59.344 --> 00:38:02.381 align:middle line:84%
the media acts like,
"Oh, what a surprise.

00:38:02.381 --> 00:38:04.549 align:middle line:90%
We had no idea."

00:38:04.549 --> 00:38:06.051 align:middle line:90%
That's not true.

00:38:06.051 --> 00:38:09.021 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: OK, let me tell you
about another whistleblower.

00:38:09.021 --> 00:38:10.021 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:38:10.021 --> 00:38:11.456 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Do you remember
what happened

00:38:11.456 --> 00:38:15.761 align:middle line:84%
with the US Postal Service
where we said that we had

00:38:15.761 --> 00:38:17.496 align:middle line:90%
to tighten their belts because--

00:38:17.496 --> 00:38:18.597 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:38:18.597 --> 00:38:20.599 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: The reason why
is because they have

00:38:20.599 --> 00:38:23.135 align:middle line:84%
to prefund all of
their pensions.

00:38:23.135 --> 00:38:25.237 align:middle line:90%
This is an accounting rule.

00:38:25.237 --> 00:38:29.908 align:middle line:84%
And then, the bankers
go out and raised funds

00:38:29.908 --> 00:38:32.310 align:middle line:84%
on the capital markets
to finance--

00:38:32.310 --> 00:38:33.712 align:middle line:90%
to prefund the pensions.

00:38:33.712 --> 00:38:37.783 align:middle line:84%
Now, these postal workers aren't
going to be retiring next year.

00:38:37.783 --> 00:38:39.184 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:38:39.184 --> 00:38:41.486 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Why should all of that
money be sitting there liquid?

00:38:41.486 --> 00:38:43.054 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: For retirement
upfront, yes.

00:38:43.054 --> 00:38:43.588 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Exactly.

00:38:43.588 --> 00:38:44.656 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:38:44.656 --> 00:38:45.557 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Why are you
financing this upfront?

00:38:45.557 --> 00:38:46.691 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:38:46.691 --> 00:38:48.994 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: The reason why
is it's a very lucrative

00:38:48.994 --> 00:38:52.497 align:middle line:84%
and it's the same thing for
municipal financing or Detroit

00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:53.799 align:middle line:90%
or any of these things.

00:38:53.799 --> 00:38:57.335 align:middle line:84%
It's very lucrative practice
for these banks to go out.

00:38:57.335 --> 00:38:59.871 align:middle line:84%
So it's the same thing--
no, I'm not saying

00:38:59.871 --> 00:39:02.340 align:middle line:84%
that Cyprus doesn't
have a financial problem

00:39:02.340 --> 00:39:05.811 align:middle line:84%
but I'm saying the
answer is not immediately

00:39:05.811 --> 00:39:07.579 align:middle line:90%
to turn to austerity.

00:39:07.579 --> 00:39:11.349 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Not only that, pilfering
the accounts of the depositors.

00:39:11.349 --> 00:39:12.751 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Yes.

00:39:12.751 --> 00:39:17.122 align:middle line:84%
This is a solution that
makes sense if you're one

00:39:17.122 --> 00:39:20.792 align:middle line:84%
of the super entity and
makes no sense if you're one

00:39:20.792 --> 00:39:22.394 align:middle line:90%
of the people living in any

00:39:22.394 --> 00:39:24.629 align:middle line:84%
of these countries that's
going into austerity.

00:39:24.629 --> 00:39:29.935 align:middle line:84%
This is why we have to have
a very serious conversation

00:39:29.935 --> 00:39:31.770 align:middle line:90%
about what the conventions are.

00:39:31.770 --> 00:39:34.139 align:middle line:84%
Because the point is,
if you're not prefund--

00:39:34.139 --> 00:39:35.273 align:middle line:84%
let's go back to
what we were talking

00:39:35.273 --> 00:39:37.375 align:middle line:84%
about with prefunding
the pensions.

00:39:37.375 --> 00:39:40.579 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have to prefund
all of these pensions,

00:39:40.579 --> 00:39:44.316 align:middle line:84%
that you don't have to tax
people to pay the debt,

00:39:44.316 --> 00:39:47.419 align:middle line:84%
the interest on these
bonds that you're issuing.

00:39:47.419 --> 00:39:48.620 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:39:48.620 --> 00:39:50.956 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Well, if the money
stays with the people,

00:39:50.956 --> 00:39:52.591 align:middle line:90%
they buy goods and services.

00:39:52.591 --> 00:39:54.559 align:middle line:90%
The economy grows.

00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:55.894 align:middle line:90%
You don't have a depression.

00:39:55.894 --> 00:39:57.562 align:middle line:90%
This is a way to get more jobs.

00:39:57.562 --> 00:39:58.163 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Keeping this circulating.

00:39:58.163 --> 00:39:58.697 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Exactly.

00:39:58.697 --> 00:39:59.831 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:39:59.831 --> 00:40:02.767 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: This is a way to
keep more jobs instead

00:40:02.767 --> 00:40:05.737 align:middle line:84%
of keep more profits
in Wall Street.

00:40:05.737 --> 00:40:09.341 align:middle line:84%
So we need to have a
monetary conference

00:40:09.341 --> 00:40:11.276 align:middle line:84%
in the Bretton Woods
Institutions

00:40:11.276 --> 00:40:13.445 align:middle line:84%
and anywhere else
that makes sense.

00:40:13.445 --> 00:40:17.983 align:middle line:84%
But, first of all, all of
the people who are thinking

00:40:17.983 --> 00:40:22.087 align:middle line:84%
that they can just relax and let
the experts take care of things,

00:40:22.087 --> 00:40:24.789 align:middle line:84%
no, they need to
inform themselves.

00:40:24.789 --> 00:40:29.060 align:middle line:84%
There's something that they
call a democratic deficit.

00:40:29.060 --> 00:40:32.130 align:middle line:84%
Your Secretary of the
Treasury is going to all

00:40:32.130 --> 00:40:34.566 align:middle line:84%
of these meetings and
speaking on your behalf.

00:40:34.566 --> 00:40:36.401 align:middle line:84%
What do you know about
what he's saying?

00:40:36.401 --> 00:40:39.170 align:middle line:84%
What do you know about
what the conventions are?

00:40:39.170 --> 00:40:41.239 align:middle line:90%
You need to inform yourself.

00:40:41.239 --> 00:40:43.308 align:middle line:90%
You need to be involved.

00:40:43.308 --> 00:40:46.011 align:middle line:84%
You need to support the
people who are trying

00:40:46.011 --> 00:40:49.614 align:middle line:84%
to get this situation
regularized

00:40:49.614 --> 00:40:53.552 align:middle line:84%
so that the shots are not being
called by this super entity.

00:40:53.552 --> 00:40:54.853 align:middle line:90%
Who elected them?

00:40:54.853 --> 00:40:58.056 align:middle line:84%
Nobody. Why should they deny
information to the public?

00:40:58.056 --> 00:40:59.324 align:middle line:90%
They shouldn't.

00:40:59.324 --> 00:41:01.293 align:middle line:90%
That's all.

00:41:01.293 --> 00:41:02.727 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:41:02.727 --> 00:41:04.296 align:middle line:84%
Well, as we talked about at the
beginning this conversation,

00:41:04.296 --> 00:41:07.032 align:middle line:84%
it's very difficult for people
to know who they can trust

00:41:07.032 --> 00:41:08.133 align:middle line:90%
with information anymore.

00:41:08.133 --> 00:41:09.734 align:middle line:90%
That's really a big one.

00:41:09.734 --> 00:41:13.572 align:middle line:84%
So when you have the super
entities creating media outlets

00:41:13.572 --> 00:41:16.875 align:middle line:84%
that are posing as alternative
media outlets for example,

00:41:16.875 --> 00:41:18.743 align:middle line:90%
this makes it even cloudier.

00:41:18.743 --> 00:41:20.946 align:middle line:84%
People almost have to go
to a crystal ball to figure

00:41:20.946 --> 00:41:23.548 align:middle line:84%
out who they can trust
and listen to any longer.

00:41:23.548 --> 00:41:25.450 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Well, what they
need to do is talk

00:41:25.450 --> 00:41:26.918 align:middle line:90%
to their next door neighbor--

00:41:26.918 --> 00:41:27.752 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:41:27.752 --> 00:41:29.154 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: -- and do a study group.

00:41:29.154 --> 00:41:30.622 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: That is very true.

00:41:30.622 --> 00:41:31.823 align:middle line:90%
Taking it to the streets

00:41:31.823 --> 00:41:34.392 align:middle line:84%
and taking responsibility
ourselves as you said.

00:41:34.392 --> 00:41:35.560 align:middle line:90%
Now, there is a group

00:41:35.560 --> 00:41:38.163 align:middle line:84%
of countries taking
responsibility themselves.

00:41:38.163 --> 00:41:40.031 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about
the BRIC countries.

00:41:40.031 --> 00:41:42.534 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
what's happening

00:41:42.534 --> 00:41:49.207 align:middle line:84%
between the super entity-- super
entities and the BRIC countries,

00:41:49.207 --> 00:41:53.311 align:middle line:84%
and why the BRIC countries, and
please talk about who they are,

00:41:53.311 --> 00:41:55.814 align:middle line:84%
why they're-- each one of
these countries is involved,

00:41:55.814 --> 00:41:58.817 align:middle line:90%
what they're attempting to do.

00:41:58.817 --> 00:42:03.588 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: That's Brazil, Russia,
India, China, and South Africa.

00:42:03.588 --> 00:42:06.191 align:middle line:84%
And these countries,
if you add up the trade

00:42:06.191 --> 00:42:10.495 align:middle line:84%
that they have among
themselves, that's 25 percent

00:42:10.495 --> 00:42:12.731 align:middle line:90%
of international trade.

00:42:12.731 --> 00:42:17.802 align:middle line:84%
So what this means is the
dollar has been the currency

00:42:17.802 --> 00:42:19.404 align:middle line:90%
for international trade.

00:42:19.404 --> 00:42:21.906 align:middle line:84%
We have been financing
all of the trade

00:42:21.906 --> 00:42:23.275 align:middle line:90%
between these countries.

00:42:23.275 --> 00:42:25.744 align:middle line:84%
They said, "You know, I
think we've had enough

00:42:25.744 --> 00:42:28.313 align:middle line:84%
of the corruption of
this super entity.

00:42:28.313 --> 00:42:32.951 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we find a different
system for financing our trade?"

00:42:32.951 --> 00:42:36.421 align:middle line:84%
And so, at the last
spring meeting just before

00:42:36.421 --> 00:42:38.690 align:middle line:84%
that in April, they
announced that they were going

00:42:38.690 --> 00:42:40.492 align:middle line:84%
to setup their own
development bank.

00:42:40.492 --> 00:42:43.828 align:middle line:84%
And what they're going to do
is they are going to add up,

00:42:43.828 --> 00:42:45.230 align:middle line:90%
they're going to use barter.

00:42:45.230 --> 00:42:49.768 align:middle line:84%
They're going to add up who's
got a positive trade balance.

00:42:49.768 --> 00:42:52.237 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to
finance that with gold

00:42:52.237 --> 00:42:57.108 align:middle line:84%
and then they're going to take
the dollars that they have got,

00:42:57.108 --> 00:43:00.745 align:middle line:84%
surplus dollars that they don't
want anymore, and they're going

00:43:00.745 --> 00:43:02.747 align:middle line:84%
to lend them out through
this development bank.

00:43:02.747 --> 00:43:06.985 align:middle line:84%
So it's a way for them to get
rid of all of these surplus--

00:43:06.985 --> 00:43:09.788 align:middle line:84%
and where are these extra
dollars coming from?

00:43:09.788 --> 00:43:12.590 align:middle line:84%
They're coming from something
called quantitative easing.

00:43:12.590 --> 00:43:13.658 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:43:13.658 --> 00:43:15.860 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: Every month,
we've got, you know,

00:43:15.860 --> 00:43:20.031 align:middle line:84%
printing press going
with paper currency.

00:43:20.031 --> 00:43:22.667 align:middle line:90%
Now, people aren't-- the demand

00:43:22.667 --> 00:43:26.538 align:middle line:84%
for the dollars is not
meeting the supply.

00:43:26.538 --> 00:43:28.573 align:middle line:90%
There is a surplus there.

00:43:28.573 --> 00:43:30.508 align:middle line:90%
And pretty soon, you're going

00:43:30.508 --> 00:43:34.312 align:middle line:84%
to risk the people will
not view these dollars as--

00:43:34.312 --> 00:43:35.246 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: As having value.

00:43:35.246 --> 00:43:35.814 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:43:35.814 --> 00:43:36.648 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Exactly.

00:43:36.648 --> 00:43:39.351 align:middle line:90%
And so we have got to find us--

00:43:39.351 --> 00:43:44.122 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't have to be no
more dollars but we have

00:43:44.122 --> 00:43:48.493 align:middle line:84%
to find a smooth
transition to replace this--

00:43:48.493 --> 00:43:50.061 align:middle line:90%
they call it fiat currency.

00:43:50.061 --> 00:43:50.929 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:43:50.929 --> 00:43:53.264 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: It's used
to be until 1971

00:43:53.264 --> 00:43:55.867 align:middle line:84%
that you could take a
dollar and you could go

00:43:55.867 --> 00:43:59.204 align:middle line:84%
to the Federal Reserve and
you would get the dollar's

00:43:59.204 --> 00:44:00.338 align:middle line:90%
equivalent in gold.

00:44:00.338 --> 00:44:01.172 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:44:01.172 --> 00:44:02.340 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: I think it was at 35--

00:44:02.340 --> 00:44:03.341 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- cents a--
every dollars an ounce.

00:44:03.341 --> 00:44:04.609 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: -- 35 dollars an ounce.

00:44:04.609 --> 00:44:06.444 align:middle line:90%
Yes. OK. And by the way,

00:44:06.444 --> 00:44:12.317 align:middle line:84%
just before the US suspended
the convertibility of dollar

00:44:12.317 --> 00:44:16.321 align:middle line:84%
into currency, that's when
you had another situation

00:44:16.321 --> 00:44:18.757 align:middle line:84%
where there was no
more leasing of gold.

00:44:18.757 --> 00:44:23.495 align:middle line:84%
So the market is signaling that
we are getting to a situation

00:44:23.495 --> 00:44:26.631 align:middle line:84%
where we have got to
try something else.

00:44:26.631 --> 00:44:27.432 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:44:27.432 --> 00:44:28.466 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: And the question is,

00:44:28.466 --> 00:44:30.268 align:middle line:84%
what are we going to
do with that time?

00:44:30.268 --> 00:44:37.142 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm telling you is that
I have been regularly in touch

00:44:37.142 --> 00:44:39.878 align:middle line:90%
with all of the governors.

00:44:39.878 --> 00:44:42.313 align:middle line:84%
I've written to them
about four or five times.

00:44:42.313 --> 00:44:44.849 align:middle line:90%
I call up their offices.

00:44:44.849 --> 00:44:46.184 align:middle line:90%
They call me up.

00:44:46.184 --> 00:44:49.821 align:middle line:84%
I've been in touch with the
188 countries and I've said

00:44:49.821 --> 00:44:52.590 align:middle line:84%
to the countries I'm in
touch with the governors.

00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:56.528 align:middle line:84%
And so, they know that we have
got a system up and running

00:44:56.528 --> 00:45:00.532 align:middle line:84%
and we have got to
make good time of the--

00:45:00.532 --> 00:45:05.136 align:middle line:84%
good advantage of the time to
come to some orderly transition.

00:45:05.136 --> 00:45:08.473 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: What about the notion
of nationalizing the currency

00:45:08.473 --> 00:45:13.411 align:middle line:84%
to basically disbanding the fed
and the United States, well,

00:45:13.411 --> 00:45:15.880 align:middle line:84%
such as in, I think is
North Dakota, isn't it?

00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:16.447 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Yes.

00:45:16.447 --> 00:45:17.549 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:45:17.549 --> 00:45:18.550 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: The notion of
states and governments--

00:45:18.550 --> 00:45:20.218 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: You've studied
well for this.

00:45:20.218 --> 00:45:23.721 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- taking back the right
to print their own currency

00:45:23.721 --> 00:45:26.491 align:middle line:90%
on behalf of and for the people.

00:45:26.491 --> 00:45:28.726 align:middle line:84%
Do you see that as
a possibility even?

00:45:28.726 --> 00:45:30.028 align:middle line:90%
I mean, many people say,

00:45:30.028 --> 00:45:32.730 align:middle line:84%
"Why can't that we did find
a way to disband the fed?

00:45:32.730 --> 00:45:33.498 align:middle line:90%
Why can't we?

00:45:33.498 --> 00:45:34.165 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Well--

00:45:34.165 --> 00:45:34.999 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Or should we?

00:45:34.999 --> 00:45:36.301 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Let's put it this way.

00:45:36.301 --> 00:45:39.103 align:middle line:84%
This is a conversation that
needs to be taking place.

00:45:39.103 --> 00:45:42.040 align:middle line:84%
In each and every state, they
need to decide whether they want

00:45:42.040 --> 00:45:46.311 align:middle line:84%
to follow the example of North
Dakota, whether they want

00:45:46.311 --> 00:45:51.616 align:middle line:84%
to do declare precious
metals as legal tender.

00:45:51.616 --> 00:45:52.617 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:45:52.617 --> 00:45:53.718 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: This is a
conversation that needs

00:45:53.718 --> 00:45:54.686 align:middle line:90%
to be taking place right now.

00:45:54.686 --> 00:45:55.787 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Now, it sounds
like this is

00:45:55.787 --> 00:45:58.356 align:middle line:84%
where the average person
can become involved

00:45:58.356 --> 00:45:59.557 align:middle line:90%
in the conversation.

00:45:59.557 --> 00:46:02.026 align:middle line:90%
We can understand that.

00:46:02.026 --> 00:46:03.127 align:middle line:90%
>> KH: Yes.

00:46:03.127 --> 00:46:05.530 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I mean, that
we can comprehend.

00:46:05.530 --> 00:46:09.534 align:middle line:84%
Tell us the consequences of
not having this conversation,

00:46:09.534 --> 00:46:12.670 align:middle line:84%
in the near future as
far as you can see it?

00:46:12.670 --> 00:46:17.041 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: The consequence is
that you have left a legacy

00:46:17.041 --> 00:46:19.711 align:middle line:84%
for your children that
you may not want them

00:46:19.711 --> 00:46:21.379 align:middle line:90%
to have, which is--

00:46:21.379 --> 00:46:22.347 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Spill it out.

00:46:22.347 --> 00:46:23.781 align:middle line:84%
>> KH: -- the super
entity is going

00:46:23.781 --> 00:46:26.751 align:middle line:90%
to decide what it wants to do.

00:46:26.751 --> 00:46:29.153 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that it may want

00:46:29.153 --> 00:46:33.391 align:middle line:90%
to do is to have FEMA camps.

00:46:33.391 --> 00:46:34.425 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:46:34.425 --> 00:46:36.661 align:middle line:84%
Now, let's go there
for a minute, OK?

00:46:36.661 --> 00:46:39.731 align:middle line:84%
One of the things you say
is that, if they continue

00:46:39.731 --> 00:46:42.433 align:middle line:84%
to manipulate currencies
and we don't have any power

00:46:42.433 --> 00:46:45.203 align:middle line:84%
over the currencies ourselves,
just these private bankers

00:46:45.203 --> 00:46:47.872 align:middle line:84%
that we call-- we're
calling the super entity,

00:46:47.872 --> 00:46:49.307 align:middle line:84%
that have their fingers
and everything,

00:46:49.307 --> 00:46:51.543 align:middle line:90%
else including the media.

